A post received today got me thinking about items uploaded to the site.  
Copyright law is strict.  That is why we must be careful with what is 
posted on Read Alphabet or uploaded in files. /A Pillow of Winds/ is 
under copyright.  It cannot be posted on our site.  Therefore, I must 
remove it and any other files which quote copyrighted material.

This is not intended to prevent anyone from posting items whether in 
Junior or Senior QS.  It is great to see people using QS and getting 
involved in promoting the alphabet.

Just make sure items you post are in the public domain, i.e. their 
copyrights have all expired.  Shakespeare&#39;s sonnets are fine.  Poetry or 
prose from the 19th century is fine.  At this point, anything you post 
should have been published prior to 1923 according to the U.S. Copyright 
Office to insure it is in the public domain.  Thanks for your understanding.

Paige Gabhart


